37struct nvkm_fifo_chan_object {
38 struct nvkm_oproxy oproxy;
39 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan;
40 int hash;
41};
42
43static int
44nvkm_fifo_chan_child_fini(struct nvkm_oproxy *base, bool suspend)
45{
46 struct nvkm_fifo_chan_object *object =
47 container_of(base, typeof(*object), oproxy);
48 struct nvkm_engine *engine = object->oproxy.object->engine;
49 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan = object->chan;
50 struct nvkm_fifo_engn *engn = &chan->engn[engine->subdev.index];
51 const char *name = nvkm_subdev_name[engine->subdev.index];
52 int ret = 0;
53
54 if (--engn->usecount)
55 return 0;
56
57 if (chan->func->engine_fini) {
58 ret = chan->func->engine_fini(chan, engine, suspend);
59 if (ret) {
60 nvif_error(&chan->object,
61 "detach %s failed, %d\n", name, ret);
62 return ret;
63 }
64 }
65
66 if (engn->object) {
67 ret = nvkm_object_fini(engn->object, suspend);
68 if (ret && suspend)
69 return ret;
70 }
71
72 nvif_trace(&chan->object, "detached %s\n", name);
73 return ret;
74}
75
76static int
77nvkm_fifo_chan_child_init(struct nvkm_oproxy *base)
78{
79 struct nvkm_fifo_chan_object *object =
80 container_of(base, typeof(*object), oproxy);
81 struct nvkm_engine *engine = object->oproxy.object->engine;
82 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan = object->chan;
83 struct nvkm_fifo_engn *engn = &chan->engn[engine->subdev.index];
84 const char *name = nvkm_subdev_name[engine->subdev.index];
85 int ret;
86
87 if (engn->usecount++)
88 return 0;
89
90 if (engn->object) {
91 ret = nvkm_object_init(engn->object);
92 if (ret)
93 return ret;
94 }
95
96 if (chan->func->engine_init) {
97 ret = chan->func->engine_init(chan, engine);
98 if (ret) {
99 nvif_error(&chan->object,
100 "attach %s failed, %d\n", name, ret);
101 return ret;
102 }
103 }
104
105 nvif_trace(&chan->object, "attached %s\n", name);
106 return 0;
107}
108
109static void
110nvkm_fifo_chan_child_del(struct nvkm_oproxy *base)
111{
112 struct nvkm_fifo_chan_object *object =
113 container_of(base, typeof(*object), oproxy);
114 struct nvkm_engine *engine = object->oproxy.base.engine;
115 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan = object->chan;
116 struct nvkm_fifo_engn *engn = &chan->engn[engine->subdev.index];
117
118 if (chan->func->object_dtor)
119 chan->func->object_dtor(chan, object->hash);
120
121 if (!--engn->refcount) {
122 if (chan->func->engine_dtor)
123 chan->func->engine_dtor(chan, engine);
124 nvkm_object_del(&engn->object);
125 if (chan->vm)
126 atomic_dec(&chan->vm->engref[engine->subdev.index]);
127 }
128}
129
130static const struct nvkm_oproxy_func
131nvkm_fifo_chan_child_func = {
132 .dtor[0] = nvkm_fifo_chan_child_del,
133 .init[0] = nvkm_fifo_chan_child_init,
134 .fini[0] = nvkm_fifo_chan_child_fini,
135};
136
137static int
138nvkm_fifo_chan_child_new(const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, void *data, u32 size,
139 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
140{
141 struct nvkm_engine *engine = oclass->engine;
142 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan = nvkm_fifo_chan(oclass->parent);
143 struct nvkm_fifo_engn *engn = &chan->engn[engine->subdev.index];
144 struct nvkm_fifo_chan_object *object;
145 int ret = 0;
146
147 if (!(object = kzalloc(sizeof(*object), GFP_KERNEL)))
148 return -ENOMEM;
149 nvkm_oproxy_ctor(&nvkm_fifo_chan_child_func, oclass, &object->oproxy);
150 object->chan = chan;
151 *pobject = &object->oproxy.base;
152
153 if (!engn->refcount++) {
154 struct nvkm_oclass cclass = {
155 .client = oclass->client,
156 .engine = oclass->engine,
157 };
158
159 if (chan->vm)
160 atomic_inc(&chan->vm->engref[engine->subdev.index]);
161
162 if (engine->func->fifo.cclass) {
163 ret = engine->func->fifo.cclass(chan, &cclass,
164 &engn->object);
165 } else
166 if (engine->func->cclass) {
167 ret = nvkm_object_new_(engine->func->cclass, &cclass,
168 NULL, 0, &engn->object);
169 }
170 if (ret)
171 return ret;
172
173 if (chan->func->engine_ctor) {
174 ret = chan->func->engine_ctor(chan, oclass->engine,
175 engn->object);
176 if (ret)
177 return ret;
178 }
179 }
180
181 ret = oclass->base.ctor(&(const struct nvkm_oclass) {
182 .base = oclass->base,
183 .engn = oclass->engn,
184 .handle = oclass->handle,
185 .object = oclass->object,
186 .client = oclass->client,
187 .parent = engn->object ?
188 engn->object :
189 oclass->parent,
190 .engine = engine,
191 }, data, size, &object->oproxy.object);
192 if (ret)
193 return ret;
194
195 if (chan->func->object_ctor) {
196 object->hash =
197 chan->func->object_ctor(chan, object->oproxy.object);
198 if (object->hash < 0)
199 return object->hash;
200 }
201
202 return 0;
203}
204
205static int
206nvkm_fifo_chan_child_get(struct nvkm_object *object, int index,
207 struct nvkm_oclass *oclass)
208{
209 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan = nvkm_fifo_chan(object);
210 struct nvkm_fifo *fifo = chan->fifo;
211 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->engine.subdev.device;
212 struct nvkm_engine *engine;
213 u64 mask = chan->engines;
214 int ret, i, c;
215
216 for (; c = 0, mask && (i = __ffs64(mask), 1); mask &= ~(1ULL << i)) {
217 if (!(engine = nvkm_device_engine(device, i)))
218 continue;
219 oclass->engine = engine;
220 oclass->base.oclass = 0;
221
222 if (engine->func->fifo.sclass) {
223 ret = engine->func->fifo.sclass(oclass, index);
224 if (oclass->base.oclass) {
225 if (!oclass->base.ctor)
226 oclass->base.ctor = nvkm_object_new;
227 oclass->ctor = nvkm_fifo_chan_child_new;
228 return 0;
229 }
230
231 index -= ret;
232 continue;
233 }
234
235 while (engine->func->sclass[c].oclass) {
236 if (c++ == index) {
237 oclass->base = engine->func->sclass[index];
238 if (!oclass->base.ctor)
239 oclass->base.ctor = nvkm_object_new;
240 oclass->ctor = nvkm_fifo_chan_child_new;
241 return 0;
242 }
243 }
244 index -= c;
245 }
246
247 return -EINVAL;
248}

250static int
251nvkm_fifo_chan_ntfy(struct nvkm_object *object, u32 type,
252 struct nvkm_event **pevent)
253{
254 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan = nvkm_fifo_chan(object);
255 if (chan->func->ntfy)
256 return chan->func->ntfy(chan, type, pevent);
257 return -ENODEV;
258}

260static int
261#ifdef __NetBSD__
262nvkm_fifo_chan_map(struct nvkm_object *object, bus_space_tag_t *tagp,
263 u64 *addr, u32 *size)
264#else
265nvkm_fifo_chan_map(struct nvkm_object *object, u64 *addr, u32 *size)
266#endif
267{
268 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan = nvkm_fifo_chan(object);
269#ifdef __NetBSD__
270 /* XXX Uh oh. Can't map this more than once. OK? */
271 *tagp = chan->bst;
272#endif
273 *addr = chan->addr;
274 *size = chan->size;
275 return 0;
276}
277
278#ifdef __NetBSD__
279static int
280nvkm_fifo_chan_ensure_mapped(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan)
281{
282 int ret;
283
284 if (likely(chan->mapped))
285 goto out;
286
287 /* XXX errno NetBSD->Linux */
288 ret = -bus_space_map(chan->bst, chan->addr, chan->size, 0,
289 &chan->bsh);
290 if (ret)
291 return ret;
292 chan->mapped = true;
293
294out: KASSERT(chan->mapped);
295 return 0;
296}
297#endif
298
299static int
300nvkm_fifo_chan_rd32(struct nvkm_object *object, u64 addr, u32 *data)
301{
302 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan = nvkm_fifo_chan(object);
303#ifdef __NetBSD__
304 int ret = nvkm_fifo_chan_ensure_mapped(chan);
305 if (ret)
306 return ret;
307#else
308 if (unlikely(!chan->user)) {
309 chan->user = ioremap(chan->addr, chan->size);
310 if (!chan->user)
311 return -ENOMEM;
312 }
313#endif
314 if (unlikely(addr + 4 > chan->size))
315 return -EINVAL;
316#ifdef __NetBSD__
317 *data = bus_space_read_stream_4(chan->bst, chan->bsh, addr);
318#else
319 *data = ioread32_native(chan->user + addr);
320#endif
321 return 0;
322}
323
324static int
325nvkm_fifo_chan_wr32(struct nvkm_object *object, u64 addr, u32 data)
326{
327 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan = nvkm_fifo_chan(object);
328#ifdef __NetBSD__
329 int ret = nvkm_fifo_chan_ensure_mapped(chan);
330 if (ret)
331 return ret;
332#else
333 if (unlikely(!chan->user)) {
334 chan->user = ioremap(chan->addr, chan->size);
335 if (!chan->user)
336 return -ENOMEM;
337 }
338#endif
339 if (unlikely(addr + 4 > chan->size))
340 return -EINVAL;
341#ifdef __NetBSD__
342 bus_space_write_stream_4(chan->bst, chan->bsh, addr, data);
343#else
344 iowrite32_native(data, chan->user + addr);
345#endif
346 return 0;
347}

360 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan = nvkm_fifo_chan(object);

365static void *
366nvkm_fifo_chan_dtor(struct nvkm_object *object)
367{
368 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan = nvkm_fifo_chan(object);
369 struct nvkm_fifo *fifo = chan->fifo;
370 void *data = chan->func->dtor(chan);
371 unsigned long flags;
372
373 spin_lock_irqsave(&fifo->lock, flags);
374 if (!list_empty(&chan->head)) {
375 __clear_bit(chan->chid, fifo->mask);
376 list_del(&chan->head);
377 }
378 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&fifo->lock, flags);
379
380#ifdef __NetBSD__
381 if (!chan->subregion && chan->mapped) {
382 bus_space_unmap(chan->bst, chan->bsh, chan->size);
383 chan->mapped = false;
384 }
385#else
386 if (chan->user)
387 iounmap(chan->user);
388#endif
389
390 nvkm_vm_ref(NULL, &chan->vm, NULL);
391
392 nvkm_gpuobj_del(&chan->push);
393 nvkm_gpuobj_del(&chan->inst);
394 return data;
395}
396
397static const struct nvkm_object_func
398nvkm_fifo_chan_func = {
399 .dtor = nvkm_fifo_chan_dtor,
400 .init = nvkm_fifo_chan_init,
401 .fini = nvkm_fifo_chan_fini,
402 .ntfy = nvkm_fifo_chan_ntfy,
403 .map = nvkm_fifo_chan_map,
404 .rd32 = nvkm_fifo_chan_rd32,
405 .wr32 = nvkm_fifo_chan_wr32,
406 .sclass = nvkm_fifo_chan_child_get,
407};
408
409int
410nvkm_fifo_chan_ctor(const struct nvkm_fifo_chan_func *func,
411 struct nvkm_fifo *fifo, u32 size, u32 align, bool zero,
412 u64 vm, u64 push, u64 engines, int bar, u32 base, u32 user,
413 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
414 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan)
415{
416 struct nvkm_client *client = oclass->client;
417 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->engine.subdev.device;
418 struct nvkm_mmu *mmu = device->mmu;
419 struct nvkm_dmaobj *dmaobj;
420 unsigned long flags;
421 int ret;
422
423 nvkm_object_ctor(&nvkm_fifo_chan_func, oclass, &chan->object);
424 chan->func = func;
425 chan->fifo = fifo;
426 chan->engines = engines;
427 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&chan->head);
428
429 /* instance memory */
430 ret = nvkm_gpuobj_new(device, size, align, zero, NULL, &chan->inst);
431 if (ret)
432 return ret;
433
434 /* allocate push buffer ctxdma instance */
435 if (push) {
436 dmaobj = nvkm_dma_search(device->dma, oclass->client, push);
437 if (!dmaobj)
438 return -ENOENT;
439
440 ret = nvkm_object_bind(&dmaobj->object, chan->inst, -16,
441 &chan->push);
442 if (ret)
443 return ret;
444 }
445
446 /* channel address space */
447 if (!vm && mmu) {
448 if (!client->vm || client->vm->mmu == mmu) {
449 ret = nvkm_vm_ref(client->vm, &chan->vm, NULL);
450 if (ret)
451 return ret;
452 } else {
453 return -EINVAL;
454 }
455 } else {
456 return -ENOENT;
457 }
458
459 /* allocate channel id */
460 spin_lock_irqsave(&fifo->lock, flags);
461 chan->chid = find_first_zero_bit(fifo->mask, NVKM_FIFO_CHID_NR);
462 if (chan->chid >= NVKM_FIFO_CHID_NR) {
463 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&fifo->lock, flags);
464 return -ENOSPC;
465 }
466 list_add(&chan->head, &fifo->chan);
467 __set_bit(chan->chid, fifo->mask);
468 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&fifo->lock, flags);
469
470 /* determine address of this channel's user registers */
471 chan->addr = device->func->resource_addr(device, bar) +
472 base + user * chan->chid;
473 chan->size = user;
474#ifdef __NetBSD__
475 if (bar == 0) {
476 /*
477 * We already map BAR 0 in the engine device base, so
478 * grab a subregion of that.
479 */
480 bus_space_tag_t mmiot = device->mmiot;
481 bus_space_handle_t mmioh = device->mmioh;
482 bus_size_t mmiosz = device->mmiosz;
483 __diagused bus_addr_t mmioaddr =
484 device->func->resource_addr(device, bar);
485
486 /* Check whether it lies inside the region. */
487 if (mmiosz < base ||
488 mmiosz - base < user * chan->chid ||
489 mmiosz - base - user * chan->chid < user) {
490 nvif_error(&chan->object, "fifo channel out of range:"
491 " base 0x%jx chid 0x%jx user 0x%jx mmiosz 0x%jx\n",
492 (uintmax_t)base,
493 (uintmax_t)chan->chid, (uintmax_t)user,
494 (uintmax_t)mmiosz);
495 return -EIO;
496 }
497 KASSERT(mmioaddr <= chan->addr);
498 KASSERT(base + user * chan->chid <= mmiosz - user);
499 KASSERT(chan->addr <= mmioaddr + (mmiosz - user));
500 KASSERT(chan->addr - mmioaddr == base + user * chan->chid);
501 /* XXX errno NetBSD->Linux */
502 ret = -bus_space_subregion(mmiot, mmioh,
503 base + user * chan->chid, user, &chan->bsh);
504 if (ret) {
505 nvif_error(&chan->object, "bus_space_subregion failed:"
506 " %d\n", ret);
507 return ret;
508 }
509 chan->bst = mmiot;
510 chan->mapped = true;
511 chan->subregion = true;
512 } else {
513 /* XXX Why does nouveau map this lazily? */
514 chan->bst = device->func->resource_tag(device, bar);
515 chan->mapped = false;
516 chan->subregion = false;
517 }
518#endif
519
520 nvkm_event_send(&fifo->cevent, 1, 0, NULL, 0);
521 return 0;
522}
